docs.text: " knock off " is exactly that : a cheap knock off of an action movie .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it's also the worst movie i have seen thus far this year .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: i figured it would be at least a couple of months before i saw the worst film of 1998 , but alas , it has already been found .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: jean-claude van damme stars as ( i think ) a designer jeans executive who discovers his half-brother has been supplying him with cheaper goods .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: rob schneider plays van damme's partner , and rochon plays . . .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: actually , i have no idea who rochon was supposed to be .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: she just sort of popped up halfway through without an explanation as to why she was there .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: many things are not explained in this film , but i do know that for some bizarre reason , van damme seemed to be doing a jackie chan impression throughout the flick .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: where chan comes off as endearing in his " normal guy " character seen in many of his films , van damme just comes off as a wimp .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: we're never given any clear explanation as to the basis for many of his actions .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: to be more clear : i did not even know who he was supposed to be until about an hour into the movie , and even then , it was not made too clear .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the film has been directed in the style of some strange film experiment gone horribly wrong .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: tsui hark ( who directed van damme's last movie , the bad , but not nearly as bad as this , " double team " ) never lets the camera rest for a second , and that's no exaggeration .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: we are even treated to a five second shot from the point of view of van damme's foot entering a shoe .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: fabulous !
docs.label: negative

docs.text: seriously , though , i have no problem with directors who want to play around with film conventions , as long as they don't get carried away .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: for example , look at sam raimi .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: " army of darkness " , one of his best movies , features some of the most inventive camera work i have ever seen , but raimi never lets the special effects get in the way of story .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: that's a concept that tsui can't seem to grasp .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the special effects and outrageous camera angles * rule * " knock off " to the point where the audience doesn't have a clue as to what's happening any more .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: another problem with the film is that it looks cheap .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the film stock used is of such low caliber that i thought i was watching one of those chinese films shown really late at night .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: and for some inexplicable reason , everyone's voice seems to have been dubbed .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: even the stars .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: and even the special effects , seemingly the only aspect of the film the director actually cared about , are inconsistent .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: for example , there is a scene in which van damme drives a car out of a window .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the car slams into the ground , and the left wheel is completely destroyed .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: seconds later , the car drives off at full speed .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: hey , i have no problem suspending my disbelief in an action movie , but a line must be drawn somewhere .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: finally , the acting .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: nobody gives a good performance in this film .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: van damme , an actor i usually like , is way off the mark playing " everyman " .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: and schneider , here to provide comic relief i assume , is totally unfunny and over acts his way through every scene .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: even the usually solid paul sorvino gives a terribly over-the-top performance as . . .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: once again , i have no idea who he was supposed to be .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: in case i haven't yet made it clear enough , " knock off " is the worst movie of van damme's career and possibly the worst movie of the decade .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: and it's not even one of those movies that's so bad it's funny .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it's too inept to be funny .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: there are no redeeming factors in " knock off " and i seriously hope that every print of this film is burned to a crisp and that somehow my memory of watching the film can be erased .
docs.label: negative
